The paper discusses a new approach to time-travel debugging for web applications, which involves accurately reproducing network interactions, asynchronous events, and visual states in a highly multithreaded browser runtime. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DL), or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
